# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **File**: `package.json`
- **Action**: Added `@vercel/analytics` (v2.0.0) as a dependency
- **Command Used**: `npm install @vercel/analytics`

### 2. Analytics Component Integration
- **File**: `src/app/layout.tsx`
- **Actions**:
  - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the `{children}` element
  - Properly formatted the JSX to maintain code readability

## Implementation Details

This project uses the **Next.js App Router** architecture with the layout file located at `src/app/layout.tsx`. The Analytics component was added to the root layout, which ensures that analytics tracking is enabled across all pages of the application.

### Code Structure
```tsx
import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en" className="dark">
      <body className={inter.className}>
        {children}
        <Analytics />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

## Verification

### Linting
- ✅ Ran ESLint on `src/app/layout.tsx` - No errors or warnings in our changes
- ⚠️ Pre-existing linting issues found in other files (not related to Analytics implementation)

### Build Status
- ⚠️ Build encountered a pre-existing error related to Supabase configuration (`supabaseUrl is required`)
- ✅ This error exists in `/dashboard` page and is unrelated to the Analytics implementation
- ✅ Our Analytics changes do not introduce any new build errors

### Lock Files
- ✅ `package-lock.json` updated automatically by npm with the new dependency

## Notes

1. The Analytics component will automatically track page views and web vitals when the application is deployed to Vercel
2. No additional configuration is required - the component works out of the box
3. Analytics data will be available in the Vercel dashboard once deployed
4. The component is placed at the end of the body tag to ensure it doesn't block page rendering

## Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency tree
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component

## Testing Recommendations
- Deploy to Vercel to verify analytics tracking is working
- Check the Vercel dashboard for incoming analytics data after deployment
- Verify that page load performance is not negatively impacted
